        Official Singles Chart on 1/5/2020

        1 May 2020 - 7 May 2020

        The Official UK Singles Chart reflects the UK’s biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1 and MTV, the Top 100 is published exclusively on OfficialCharts.com. View the biggest songs of 2024 so far.

        WEEKLY CHART REVIEW (01/05/2020 - 07/05/2020)

        This week, we got one of the busiest charts of the year so far, but it’s also easily one of the best!

        Obviously, the news that’ll grab the headlines is the new #1. Like last week, it’s a highly significant moment not only for Official Chart history, but also in the fight against Covid-19! As for the chart highlights… well, it’s the first time a charity single has replaced another at the top since November 2014, it's among one of the biggest debut weeks of 2020 so far, it gives 12 acts their first #1 single in the country (stated in another comment) & it’s the first ever #1 single for Radio 1 as a whole.

        As for my opinion on the song itself, man, it’s something special! To be honest, the fact that how the lyrics cover a Foo Fighters classic in how love & persistence will get us through these unusual times is inspiring enough, but what really sounds out about this charity single are the artists! Outside of the incredible passion of AJ Tracey’s rap verse, the artists here seem to be either pop or rock, but there’s also a mix of household names & upcoming artists, as well as a mix of British & international names that are big in music right now. So many artists here are making different styles of music, so the fact that the harmonisation is perfect here just blew me away entirely & especially that the emotion all of the artists are showing is only highlighted over the twinkling production, which somehow gives this an even more magical feel, especially when you consider some artists here recorded this over an iPhone or computer rather than in an expensive studio! My only criticism is that they only gave Sigrid two words to herself because she deserves so much more than that given her talent, but I’m still delighted she’s here regardless. Ultimately, the biggest winner to this song is that it’s raising even more money for the people who need it most right now! You know something special has happened when this song even hits #1 on Radio 1’s rival chart show & I absolutely adore this collaborative effort too, especially when it’s for such a powerful cause… strong 9/10!

        However, that’s somehow not even the best debut of the week for me, because my goodness! I’ve been showing huge support for The 1975 for a while now in the build-up to their upcoming fourth studio album later this month, but this might be among the highlights of their discography for me. Again, one of the things I respect Matty Healy for as a frontman is his honesty & how he’s so open about his personal issues, but in a way that reassures others who are going through the same thing, instead of just shoving those issues in your face! Now, on the surface, you’d just think this was another song where a girl trying to get intimate with him & he certainly wants to interact with her sensually… but is too nervous to get to know her on a personal level! You can see that he’s actually trying to make an effort to get closer to her, rather than just taking her to bed & moving on, like entirely too many songs on this chart are filled off. Even then, along with Matty Healy just being able to sell this really convincingly, the production is what really stunned me here! I’ve always thought The 1975 made their most compelling music when they made up-tempo, arena rock smashes, but what makes this different to all of those are the heavier rollicks of guitar & the blaring horns, along with a sax solo in the bridge that gave me ‘The Sound’ flashbacks, you know, one of their signature hits. Once again, despite being a pop-rock band, they threw in some jazz elements here & it still rocked! Yeah, it only took me a couple of listens to understand why this was a fan favourite at the concerts the band did at the start of the year, because it’s amazing! It’s a shame it didn’t become the Top 10 like the update suggested it might. It will get from me though, 10/10!

        So those were the two new entries which I just had to rave about, now onto the songs that I won’t do full reviews for…

        Firstly, there are still two more songs that I wouldn’t say I love, but still like! The first being ‘Kings & Queens’ finally breaking into the Top 40 after two weeks of barely missing out. With this, it’s kind of feminist anthem that actually has some punch to it, with a mix of ABBA & Lady Gaga inspired production that’d be the ideal fit for discos whenever this lockdown ends. Not only that, but Ava Max continues to show off her consistently impressive vocal range! Strong 8/10 for this one.

        The other big climber that makes a gain into the Top 40 for the first time is the newest dance smash with even more momentum, ‘Don’t Need Love’ by 220KID & Gracey! Unlike most rising bangers, this is the kind of one that would’ve hit the club scene a lot quicker if it weren’t for the lockdown, especially with the fuzzy & spacy drop courtesy of 220KID. Even Gracey provides the right kind of dark melody for this, as she describes how lonely she is in general, but still tries to be adventurous when she’s out. In other words, whether or not things start to return to normal over the summer, I have the feeling a lot of EDM fans will be blasting this over the next few months, including me! Solid 8/10.

        As for the rap songs, starting with ‘Houdini’, woah… what an improvement over ‘Poppin’! Okay, I know you can’t exactly get much worse than that song, haha, but in all seriousness, this is genuinely decent & I’m amazed that it charted this high given his chart run with his most recent singles. I guess the two big changes are swapping out the imcopentent American rappers Lil Pump & Smokepurpp with insufferable trap production, for two new grime artists & a tropical beat that really packs a punch, making the bragging actually sound fun for once. Light 7/10!

        I’d even give ‘Righteous’ a pass too! The smoother trap beat & guitar plucks that open the song immediately told me that this is going to have a much more depressing tone, but what really brought me with a moment of sadness is how the content describes Juice WRLD’s battle with drugs & that he knew it could all end very soon, which is unfortunately what happened. The disappointing part is that this could've been the point where I was really won over by his music, but his voice… I’m sorry, I’ll never get behind that with the painful wailing which has never really changed from him, even when he was alive! That’s going to knock some points off sadly, but it’s still not bad by any means & at least I understand the appeal more, even if it’s still not my kind of music. Light 6/10!

        Unfortunately, one debut that won’t be getting a high score at all is ‘The Scotts’! I feel like every song that Travis Scott releases is slathered with auto-tune & takes stabs at law enforcement or their opponents, which doesn’t really give me any signs of artistic development here. Even Kid Cudi doesn’t sound all that memorable over the grating synthesizer which alternates between having a dull crisp sound, to a twinkle that is pitched so high that it almost drowns everything else out, even the bassline! There’s apparently some hype behind this among critics, but no, not me, not at all. Strong 2/10!

        Other things I want to shout-out about this week is Dua Lipa technically getting the chart double, as she part of the #1 song of the week & has the #1 album of the week all to herself! I’m also pleased to see ‘Death Bed’ finally in the Top 5.

        Next week, expect ‘Savage’ & ‘Say So’ to get considerable gains thanks to both hits getting remixes, while ‘Times Like These’ could contend for another week at #1 looking at how well the sales numbers are holding up (although it’s going to be tight!).

        As always, stay safe everyone! :)

        🧡 oliviasnoodles 🍜
